&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM UNTIL JUNE 2021 DUE TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the NHS Wales National Collaborative Commissioning Unit. Our Quality Assurance Improvement Service have obtained temporary funding for a clinical research post to support the wider clinical team with developing new national standards for upcoming new National Hospital Framework Agreements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will support the current clinical and performance teams to develop and enhance standards that will be based on current best practice and evidence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 12th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Adrian Clarke, Assistant. Director of Nursing &amp; Quality&lt;br /&gt;adrian.clarke2@wales.nhs.uk&lt;br /&gt;07805812113&lt;/p&gt;
